<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#800000">Originally posted by Cydrenlin on 09-15-2000 09:53 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hummm i will be flamed for my opinion but I need to tell it.

I think that price on some items can have a LOT of difference from day to day, server to server, people to people. I want to buy a langseax (it s my first char, i am not twinked but i am in a guild who helped me with banded armor  :) ). I have something like 35pp. Don't laugh at me ! The fact is that when i look to the prices here on the web, i see "langseax 22-30 pp" ... Ok, so i should be able to buy one because 35>30 ..
Not at all. It's impossible ! No one sell them for 30 pp !! I mean the lowest offer i got was 60 pp (30pp * 2) and the highest was 90 pp (30pp * 3).

I won't buy at this price because i will give money to "professionnal traders" and i think it's stupid. They can keep their "unvaluable magical items" ....

So i said to my self: "Don't be shy, read the quest description and let's do this quest." Didn't seems to be very hard so let's go... Except than i am a Dark Elf ! (My faction with these big-dumb barbarians is not very good by default hehe). So i still use a FS scimetar (the guild gave me) and a bronze long sword.

Is the fault to the wed site with these kind of prices ? To these "professionnal traders" ? Maybee i am stupid and not-fully-capitalist (i am not american hehe) but i think this system is very difficult for the new people in game because we don't have the time/experience needed to know if this langseax is worth 30, 60 or 90 pp.. All i kow is that i cannot get it by "normal means" (doing the quest).

~~Cydrenlin~~
~~A lvl 15 Dark Elf Warrior that will get a langseax sooner or later and for no more than 30pp or in doing the quest myself~~
</TEXTAREA>
